rranean counterparts, and contextualizing them within the identity crisis that followed the disintegration of the Roman world. This approach leads to groundbreaking conclusions about Gregory’s hagiographies, which this study argues were designed as an “ecclesiastical history” (of the Merovingian Church) that enabled him to craft a specific Gallo-Christian identity for his audience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHistorianszFrance. 0aMiddle Ages. 4aAntiquity. 4aEuropean history: medieval period, middle ages. 4aEuropean history: the Celts. 4aEuropean history: the Romans. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aMedieval Studies. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh  aHagiography, Identity, Merovingians, Ecclesiastical History, Cults of Saints, Early Middle Ages.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishz978311075405608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z9783110753813oZDB-23-DGD40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048551996?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048551996423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048551996/original  a978-3-11-074322-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075405-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aE